  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/5134",
  "title": "feat(routing): include repeated indexId in URL correctly",
  "body": "Before this PR the deepest nested indexId takes \"complete control\" of its indexId, and thus widgets mounted deeper didn't get \"registered\"\r\n\r\nAdded a new test to the existing getUiState describe, as well as an e2e-style \"routing has correct url\" file that can be used for other cases later.\r\n\r\nCR-2067\r\n\r\nFX-1821\r\n\r\nOne thing to consider is whether this is a breaking change. Before this change, URLs would have only \"the last index with that id\" (which was wrong), but now it'll include the correct ui state\r\n",
